@startuml configuration-flow
' Diagram scope rule for future regeneration:
' Keep this image focused on packages that process user data requests from
' SegmentIndex to Segment: put, get, delete, and iterator/getStream paths.
' Do not add broad cross-cutting packages such as core.bootstrap,
' runtimemonitoring/monitoring, logging adapters, executorregistry,
' configuration, or tuning unless the image is specifically about those
' packages. They relate to many packages and obscure the request path.
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
top to bottom direction

title SegmentIndex Request Processing Package Relationships

component "Public API\nsegmentindex\n\nSegmentIndex\nput / get / delete / getStream" as Api

component "Session boundary\ncore.session\n\nSegmentIndexImpl\nSegmentIndexPointOperationFacade\nSegmentIndexReadFacade" as Session

package "Point operations" {
  component "Operation coordinator\ncore.operations\n\nIndexOperationCoordinator" as Operations
  component "Storage boundary\ncore.storage\n\nStorageService\nappendWalPut / appendWalDelete" as Storage
}

package "Iterator operations" {
  component "Iterator access\ncore.session + core.streaming\n\nSegmentTopologyRuntimeAccess\nDirectSegmentCoordinator\nSegmentStreamingService" as Streaming
  component "Stable segment access\ncore.stablesegment\n\nStableSegmentOperationGateway" as StableAccess
}

package "Routing and segment access" {
  component "Route lease service\ncore.segmentlease\n\nSegmentLeaseService" as LeaseService
  component "Route state\nmapping + core.topology\n\nKeyToSegmentMap\nSegmentTopology" as RouteState
  component "Segment registry\nsegmentregistry\n\nSegmentRegistry\nBlockingSegment" as SegmentRegistry
}

component "Segment engine\nsegment\n\nSegment\nSegmentImpl" as Segment

Api --> Session : public user calls
Session --> Operations : put / get / delete
Session --> Streaming : iterator / getStream

Operations --> Storage : append WAL for writes
Operations --> LeaseService : route key and acquire segment
LeaseService --> RouteState : key-to-segment lookup\nand route lease
LeaseService --> SegmentRegistry : load segment handle

Streaming --> RouteState : segment ids and windows
Streaming --> StableAccess : open iterator
StableAccess --> SegmentRegistry : tryGetSegment

SegmentRegistry --> Segment : get / put / openIterator

legend bottom
Scope: packages on the user request path to Segment only.
Cross-cutting packages such as bootstrap, monitoring, logging, executors,
configuration, and tuning are intentionally excluded from this image.
endlegend
@enduml
